MedMNIST Experiment Results Analysis

This notebook analyzes the results of the variability and similarity experiments on MedMNIST datasets using pre-trained diffusion models.

Variability vs Similarity

Scatter plot showing the relationship between dataset variability (Mean Squared Distance to Centroid) and similarity score (FID).
  • Variability: Higher values indicate more diverse datasets
  • Similarity (FID): Lower values indicate generated images closer to real ones
